abstract: IT'S just another ripple in the no-longer-tranquil sea  of men's fashion, but batten down the hatches and watch it roll. The trend toward fur coats for men has been doing poorly in modern times--except for periodic and minimal outbreaks of jazz-age raccoon --but the more adventurous furriers are determined to tempt the male customer this year. Meanwhile, they're hoping for a cold winter.
headline_main: Men in Furs? After All, It Started with the Caveman

abstract: YONKERS, Aug. 27--Trader Horn Inc., the name under which Mr. and Mrs. Arthur Nardin of North Bay Village, Fla., conducts its harness racing business, didn't fare too badly in tonight's co-feature races at Yonkers Raceway. Nor did Billy Haughton, who trains and drives for the Nardins.

abstract: WILLIAMSPORT, Pa. Aug. 26 (UPI) Kankakee, Ill., defeated Monterrey, Mexico, 2-1, today for fifth-place honors in the 20th annual Little League World Series. The winning run was scored on a throwing error in the sixth and final inning.
